cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.SE

This paper focuses on the performance of deep learning based radio signal classification for radio communications signals. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also compares the performance of different approaches and considers the effects of channel impairments, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses remaining problems and design considerations, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
